<HEADLINE>
<P>
STEELER FAN BEATEN AT RAIDERS GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have been an avid Raider fan since the day the team arrived from Oakland. I 
do not believe it is fair to judge all Raider fans or the Coliseum as a place 
where "hooligans" gather. 
</P>
<P>
Unlike the riots that occur at English soccer matches, this was an isolated 
incident. The Los Angeles Police Department and the Coliseum security staff do 
a fine job of controlling the crowd. 
</P>
<P>
I strongly believe that new rules should be drawn up that prohibit the sale of 
any alcoholic beverages after the second quarter, and possibly permit a maximum 
of two beers per customer at all games league-wide. 
</P>
<P>
I ask that the media and everyone in general not allow "one bad apple to spoil 
the whole bunch of us." 
</P>
<P>
GILBERT DE ALBA 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
