PRO FOOTBALL REPORT WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
RAMS; 
</P>
<P>
DUPREE GETS A TRYOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Running back Marcus Dupree showed up at Rams Park Monday, five years since he 
last played football. 
</P>
<P>
"It'd be like 'The Natural,' wouldn't it?" Coach John Robinson said of the 
improbable comeback attempt. 
</P>
<P>
Dupree, who sustained what everybody agreed at the time was a career-ending 
knee injury while playing for the United States Football League's Portland 
Breakers in 1985, still has a lot to prove, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Dupree apparently passed a physical exam Sunday. The Rams worked him out Monday 
and were giving his reconstructed knee a more complex exam later in the day. 
</P>
<P>
"It's been five years since I stepped on a football field," Dupree, 26, said. 
TIM KAWAKAMI 
