<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: KCET WINS GOVERNOR'S AWARD FOR RIDE-SHARING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KCET in Los Angeles has been awarded the Governor's Transportation Award 1990, 
in the category of outstanding achievement, for the station's ride-sharing 
program. 
</P>
<P>
KCET offers employees who share rides two extra vacation days, a guaranteed 
ride home, flextime and the option of tele-commuting. More than 25% of KCET's 
295 full-time employees participate in car-pooling, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The award was announced in advance of RideShare week, which began on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
