<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ventura County population has grown, but the percentage of workers in different 
industries has remained fairly constant, except for service and government 
workers. Financial analyst Steven D. Cummings said the steady decline in the 
percentage of government workers came after the taxpayer revolt, Proposition 
13, which restricted government revenues. 
</P>
