<P>
AMD Introduces New Chips: A new breed of microprocessors developed by Advanced 
Micro Devices Corp. combines on a single piece of silicon many components 
needed for an IBM-compatible personal computer. The so-called semi-computers 
can match the function of entire circuit boards containing anywhere from a 
handful of chips to 175 separate integrated circuits. The technology is 
expected to spawn a new generation of smaller and less expensive personal 
computers. 
</P>
