<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: SANFORD KANE NAMED CHIEF OF PCO INC. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sanford L. Kane, former head of the aborted U.S. Memories semiconductor 
venture, has been named president and chief executive of Chatsworth-based PCO 
Inc. 
</P>
<P>
PCO, a joint venture between Corning Inc. and International Business Machines, 
manufactures optoelectronic interfaces, a key component in the operation of 
fiber optic technology used in telecommunications and other applications. 
</P>
<P>
The appointment of Kane, 48, "will assist the firm as it drives toward 
achieving higher volume manufacturing levels, developing a mainline portfolio 
and expanding support for key customers," PCO said. 
</P>
<P>
Kane, a longtime IBM executive, had most recently been chief executive and 
president of U.S. Memories, a venture to manufacture advanced dynamic random 
access memory (DRAM) chips that was aborted after gaining insufficient 
financial support from semiconductor firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
