<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: ASOLO, ITALY; 
</P>
<P>
TOUGH TOPICS FOR EUROPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the 12-member European Community will tackle two tough 
questions -- the Persian Gulf crisis and the political union of the Continent 
-- at a special three-day meeting in the northern Italian town of Asolo 
beginning Friday. 
</P>
<P>
In a follow-up to the last EC summit meeting in Dublin, the foreign ministers 
are expected to explore various plans for establishing a closer political 
grouping among the nations of Western Europe -- a move resisted by Britain, and 
more recently, West Germany. 
</P>
<P>
That topic, however, will be overshadowed by discussions of the amount of 
assistance the European nations should provide in the gulf crisis, and the 
damage that a full-scale war could to do Western European economies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
