<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
LIBERIA; 
</P>
<P>
TASK FORCE STRIKES REBEL POSITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heavy fighting was reported in the Liberian capital of Monrovia after a West 
African peacekeeping task force, backed by Nigerian warplanes and heavy 
artillery, opened fire on Charles Taylor's rebel army in at least two suburban 
locations, including a key airfield held by the rebels. The task force also 
began taking up positions around the executive mansion, where about 1,000 
soldiers from the army of slain President Samuel K. Doe remain holed up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
