<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FLORIDA; 
</P>
<P>
GUIDANCE SATELLITE BOOSTED TO ORBIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A $30-million Delta 2 rocket was launched from Cape Canaveral, Fla., to boost a 
$65-million military navigation satellite into orbit. The rocket's payload was 
a Global Positioning System Navstar satellite, the ninth in a planned network 
of such spacecraft that ultimately will allow military forces to determine 
their location and altitude to within 53 feet anywhere in the world. The flight 
plan called for the satellite to be ejected into a preliminary elliptical 
orbit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
