</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
AROUND THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brigham Young quarterback Ty Detmer has been fitted with a removable cast and 
will miss practice this week because of an injury to his throwing hand, team 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The junior quarterback passed for 442 yards but threw five interceptions in 
11th-ranked BYU's 32-16 loss at Oregon on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars (4-1) do not play this week. 
</P>
<P>
Auburn Coach Pat Dye, 50, hospitalized Sunday night for stomach pains, is 
expected to remain hospitalized for several days while he undergoes treatment 
for a problem called "pre-ulcerous." . . . Louisiana State running back Harvey 
Williams, 23, was arrested for simple battery hours after helping LSU to a 17-8 
victory over Texas A&amp;M. His wife, Lorie, accused him of choking her "and 
officers did witness red marks on her neck," Baton Rouge, La., police spokesman 
Jeff Wesley said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
