<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
UCLA; 
</P>
<P>
ERROR COULD HAVE COST GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UCLA had to settle for a field goal against Washington State Saturday night in 
the third quarter after driving to the one-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
The Bruins were assessed a 15-yard penalty for having 12 men on the field. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a good call," Coach Terry Donahue said. "It was a game-administration 
mistake and it shouldn't happen. It could have cost us the game." 
</P>
<P>
Instead of scoring a touchdown, UCLA trailed, 20-13. But the Bruins went on to 
score 17 points in the fourth quarter. MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
