</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOVIET JEWISH IMMIGRANTS SET NEW RECORDS IN ISRAEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 18,000 Soviet Jews immigrated to Israel in September, bringing the 
total for the year to more than 100,000 for an all-time record, the National 
Conference on Soviet Jewry said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Last month's immigration figure of 18,725 surpassed the previous record of 
17,484 in August. So far, the total for 1990 is 100,926. 
</P>
<P>
The conference is a coalition of 45 national Jewish organizations and more than 
300 local community councils and federations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
