<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE DESTROYS HISTORIC HOTEL IN SANTA CRUZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA CRUZ 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An old hotel that became the center of a preservation battle after it was 
closed after last year's earthquake has been gutted by fire. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters were investigating the cause of the blaze Sunday at the 
95-year-old St. George Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
Gas and electricity had been turned off since the hotel was boarded up after 
the Oct. 17 earthquake. 
</P>
