<P>
CLIPPERS SIGN MICHIGAN FORWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Loy Vaught, the 13th player taken in the latest NBA draft, signed a reported 
$4-million, 4-year contract with the Los Angeles Clippers today. 
</P>
<P>
Vaught, a 6-foot-9 power forward out of the University of Michigan, was the 
second of two first-round picks by the Clippers in the draft. 
</P>
<P>
They took Bo Kimble, the former Loyola Marymount star, with the No. 8 pick. 
Kimble remains unsigned. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm very excited to be a Clipper," Vaught said. "This team has so much talent 
and potential." 
</P>
<P>
"We're very ecstatic to have him in training camp," said Mike Schuler, the 
Clippers' new coach. "It can be such a big advantage for a rookie. 
</P>
<P>
"He's a tremendous young man and we expect him to make a contribution right 
away." 
</P>
<P>
The Clippers open training camp Friday at nearby Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
</TEXT>
